/*]]>*/</style>
<div class=3D"toc-macro rbtoc1744058934470">
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">
<li><a href=3D"#BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-Slidedeck">Slide deck</a></=
li>
<li><a href=3D"#BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-Abstract">Abstract</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-Problem">Problem</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-Solution">Solution</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-TechnicalSpecifications">Te=
chnical Specifications</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-ProblemsandChallenges">Prob=
lems and Challenges</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-AdditionalUseCases">Additio=
nal Use Cases</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"#BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-QuestionsandIdeas">Question=
s and Ideas</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-Slidedeck">Slide deck</h1>
<p><a href=3D"https://tmobileusa-my.sharepoint.com/:p:/g/personal/brendan_w=
are7_t-mobile_com/EU46VtePKOxCpgjo1ohCPwIBRHrF4WZgLAvT1WABlaok8Q?e=3DgvUp7y=
" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
https://tmobileusa-my.sharepoint.com/:p:/g/personal/brendan_ware7_t-mobile_=
com/EU46VtePKOxCpgjo1ohCPwIBRHrF4WZgLAvT1WABlaok8Q?e=3DgvUp7y</a></p>
<h1 id=3D"BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-Abstract">Abstract</h1>
<p>Rideshare and RMN kiosks both show ads to users nearby, either in the st=
ore or in the car. However, we have very limited ability to determine who t=
he user viewing the ad is, or their dwell time in the store. This causes pr=
oblems with ad attribution and limits the data we can use to drive ad decis=
ions or use in Measurement. If we can leverage the existing T-Mobile apps t=
o broadcast an encrypted identifier, we can leverage our in-house data to c=
ollect useful advertising metrics for users in RMN stores or Rideshare ride=
s.</p>
<h1 id=3D"BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-Problem">Problem</h1>
<p>The audience of a Rideshare ad is currently opaque to advertisers. Becau=
se we have no integration with Uber/Lyft, we have no information on the rid=
er, and therefor can=E2=80=99t tie them viewing the ad to an ad impression.=
 This means we can=E2=80=99t generate ad conversions off of ads shown on Ri=
deshare tablets (without specific integrations embedded in the ad), and pre=
vents us from presenting to Rideshare customers information on how effectiv=
e their ad is.</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-cen=
ter-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embed=
ded-image image-center" alt=3D"Untitled Diagram-Page-1.drawio.png" width=3D=
"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"28fe562bc91da24dd08a5e9385f21561c4d0266b4a474=
156d61d094aa9a1ea3e" data-image-src=3D"https://t-ads.atlassian.net/wiki/dow=
nload/attachments/3009511639/Untitled%20Diagram-Page-1.drawio.png?version=
=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1707249884008&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2=
" data-height=3D"121" data-width=3D"500" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0=
" data-linked-resource-id=3D"3009773759" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1"=
 data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alia=
s=3D"Untitled Diagram-Page-1.drawio.png" data-base-url=3D"https://t-ads.atl=
assian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linke=
d-resource-container-id=3D"3009511639" data-linked-resource-container-versi=
on=3D"5" data-media-id=3D"c0b9b758-8939-4644-801a-8195cc32a770" data-media-=
type=3D"file" height=3D"113"></span>
<h1 id=3D"BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-Solution">Solution</h1>
<p>The Rideshare tablet has essentially full access to the OS of the device=
. Additionally, the Adapt app has fairly deep access to the device. Similar=
 to the technology used for contact tracing during the pandemic, we could h=
ave the Adapt app send a small, low-power Bluetooth signal that contains an=
 encrypted identifier. If the device is near (within several feet) of a Rid=
eshare tablet, the tablet picks up that token, and can connect it with the =
ad shown. This gets sent to our servers, where the key is decrypted to crea=
te a Carrier ID and record the ad impression</p>
<h1 id=3D"BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-TechnicalSpecifications">Technica=
l Specifications</h1>
<p>The implementation would be using a modified version of the <a href=3D"h=
ttps://github.com/opentrace-community/opentrace-android" class=3D"external-=
link" rel=3D"nofollow">OpenTrace Open Source technology</a>, which was used=
 by both Apple and Google to facilitate contact tracing during the Covid Pa=
ndemic. At a high-level, two Bluetooth devices constantly send a low-power =
Bluetooth signal with a rolling key to prevent tracing via looking for repe=
ated keys over time. The device stores the keys it sees in a given period o=
f time, and periodically checks an external server to see if any of the key=
s it has seen are flagged. If so, it alerts the user.</p>
<p>Instead of having both devices collect data, we would just have the tabl=
et collect data, and the encrypted key would never be decrypted by the devi=
ce. Instead, it would send the key to a server, along with the ad data. The=
 server would then decrypt that key, convert it into a Carrier ID, and then=
 record the ad impression.</p>
<p>From there, other solutions to collect a Carrier ID via a conversion pix=
el would be used to tie any Rideshare ad impressions to conversions.</p>
<h1 id=3D"BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-ProblemsandChallenges">Problems a=
nd Challenges</h1>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Privacy</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Can we get sign-off from the privacy team to do this?</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The data is never shared with 3rd parties, and can=E2=80=99t be used to =
=E2=80=98trace' and individual user</p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p>Would this require specific opt-in?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Would this change the permission levels that Adapt requests on install (=
if any?)</p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p>Need to prove out the concept on the Android app(s)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Limited data set</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Only works on:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>T-Mobile devices</p></li>
<li>
<p>Running Android</p></li>
<li>
<p>With the Adapt app installed</p></li>
</ol></li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<h1 id=3D"BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-AdditionalUseCases">Additional Us=
e Cases</h1>
<p>Rideshare is the most straight-forward use case, but if the concept is p=
roved out, we could expand to other DOOH ads. The next step could be expand=
ing to devices in T-Mobile stores, or any T-Mobile owned DOOH platforms whe=
re we own the hardware. While we have location data and can marry that to a=
d showings, this can be easily limited due to privacy concerns or because o=
f how imprecise GPS can be.</p>
<p></p>
<h1 id=3D"BluetoothLowEnergyAdAttribution-QuestionsandIdeas">Questions and =
Ideas</h1>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d3=
f6e973-05a7-4ac3-9af6-5c0ffa7381dd" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 240.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 519.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Question/Idea</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Comments</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>What experiments should we run?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Test BLE range:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Perhaps set up a simulated store in the office so that we can test behav=
ior as a device moves around within the space.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>BLE broadcast behavior</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>How does BLB broadcasting work when an app is not active? Should test on=
 both iOS and Android</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Permissions</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Need to make sure we fully understand the permissions needed on both And=
roid and iOS. Of the apps we=E2=80=99re considering integrating with, T-Lif=
e and Adapt, do they already have these permissions or will we need to add =
new permissions?</p>
<p>Location tracking - there is a flag on Android to say if you are using l=
ocation tracking with BLE. Need to research on iOS. For privacy, we may wan=
t to disable location tracking.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
